            <div class="Presentation-description-wrapper"><div class="Presentation-description"><strong>My name is William Barbier, I was born in January 2000 in the surroundings of Paris, it is since my first years that I fell into the video-gaming universe, and the web
            </strong>
My childhood was full of adventures, stories of every kind, having to find princesses and exterminate monsters. Fables and tales told by passionate people. That’s where my desire to tell stories comes from in my own way, and therefore my creativity. Some say that’s where my eccentricity comes from.

I begin to apprehend the web very early on the old computer which rotated in turn, when my brothers would leave it to me. It is from this moment that my passion for the Internet, its history and its culture is confirmed.

It is therefore quite natural that after my baccalaureate in literature I began to become in my turn, a creator, by training myself autonomously on the platforms that have made my entertainment until then, but that today give me the necessary tools to evolve.

In my race, some companies saw a certain potential to trust me, to work with them, and for others, to train me, even internationally.

Today, Qyu is what represents my name as a creator, in audiovisual and graphic production.
            </div></div>
